<span id="freeTextContainer711040569630709305">The book is a piece of art, the way the writer narrates historical events in an amusing way makes this book a page turner... <br/><br/>going into the depth of it&apos;s events, you find your heart wrenched with every paper flipped, you feel sad for humanity in general, the savageness of people, the weakness of Arabs, the loss of pure belief that the higher power brings only good deeds, the irony of those speaking in the name of religion to serve their brutality and greed. <br/>You get to know that history is nothin</span>
  <span id="freeText711040569630709305" style="display:none">The book is a piece of art, the way the writer narrates historical events in an amusing way makes this book a page turner... <br /><br />going into the depth of it's events, you find your heart wrenched with every paper flipped, you feel sad for humanity in general, the savageness of people, the weakness of Arabs, the loss of pure belief that the higher power brings only good deeds, the irony of those speaking in the name of religion to serve their brutality and greed. <br />You get to know that history is nothing but a short movie that keeps on repeating itself, you understand the ugliness of humans, and their stupidity, you start questioning the reason of existence ending up with jammed thoughts in your brain and tired spirit... may God grant us the wisdom to accept what can't be changed and change what can't be accepted, for I can tell that we(as Arabs) are holding on to an invisible thread resembled in faith, hoping for a better day.<br /><br />Also i'd like to emphasis on the fact that the more divided we are the more in depth we're dawning, nothing would change this fact but ourselves, nothing would wake us up but our own minds... I just wish from the bottom of my heart that people would start differentiating between politics and religion and would stop using religion as a tool of hypnosis on the narrow minded crowds.<br /> </span>
  <a data-text-id="711040569630709305" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

