    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_503882760" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/503882760" />
    <a title="Amr Heikal" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/14570642-amr-heikal"><img alt="Amr Heikal" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/m_50x66-82093808bca726cb3249a493fbd3bd0f.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/503882760?book_show_action=true">Jan 12, 2013</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Amr Heikal" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Amr Heikal" href="/user/show/14570642-amr-heikal">Amr Heikal</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer503882760" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15831408846435293828">I heard so much about this book that I got so excited when I managed to find it in a book fair. The ideas of the stories are great, and the time period is very interesting as I had no idea about what happened in this era of history. <br/>Jut to summarize I did not enjoy the book simply because after I finished reading it I felt frustrated. So many characters but the follow through on the characters is not there. Also the descriptions of the events are very shallow, the authors passes very quickly and</span>
  <span id="freeText15831408846435293828" style="display:none">I heard so much about this book that I got so excited when I managed to find it in a book fair. The ideas of the stories are great, and the time period is very interesting as I had no idea about what happened in this era of history. <br />Jut to summarize I did not enjoy the book simply because after I finished reading it I felt frustrated. So many characters but the follow through on the characters is not there. Also the descriptions of the events are very shallow, the authors passes very quickly and ignores to tell us what went on, which leaves the reader with allot of frustration. What did Saad go through? What happened to Hisham? What happened to Jose after he betrayed Aly? Why did Aly fall in love with Fada? What happened to her after he left? What happened to Naim when he went to meet his future father in law? What happened to his wife and kids? etc etc.... The fact that Aly falls in love with Fada the mother of his best friend then falls in love with Kawthar who is a child shows that there is something fucked up in his brain but the author does not go there at all...</span>
  <a data-text-id="15831408846435293828" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

