    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_1958052947" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1958052947" />
    <a title="Toqa Muhammad" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/32048496-toqa-muhammad"><img alt="Toqa Muhammad" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1440687751p2/32048496.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1958052947?book_show_action=true">Aug 30, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Toqa Muhammad" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Toqa Muhammad" href="/user/show/32048496-toqa-muhammad">Toqa Muhammad</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1958052947" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16842570316068711043">A masterful piece of art. It has been a while since I have read something so powerful ad gripping that I feel actual pain. I am the kind of person who fears sudden change, so when I experienced the sudden changes (they are crimes actually) that the muslim Arabs of Al-Andalus had to endure, I was in so much pain that I cried! A whole nation was stripped of it&apos;s life, religion, traditions, language, names, and everything they have known their whole life. A whole nation&apos;s identity was stolen. It fr</span>
  <span id="freeText16842570316068711043" style="display:none">A masterful piece of art. It has been a while since I have read something so powerful ad gripping that I feel actual pain. I am the kind of person who fears sudden change, so when I experienced the sudden changes (they are crimes actually) that the muslim Arabs of Al-Andalus had to endure, I was in so much pain that I cried! A whole nation was stripped of it's life, religion, traditions, language, names, and everything they have known their whole life. A whole nation's identity was stolen. It frightened me how they were forcibly made to adopt foreign names, foreign way of dress, and foreign language; they were even forced to through away the scientific heritage that their ancestors have left them. All of these details cut me to the core.<br />Radwa Ashour is really a master of narration. It flows so smoothly, it is incredibly engaging and it is honest. She chose the right narrative voice for this novel (the omniscient narrator), as it gives an insight to every individuals thoughts and feelings which makes it easier to draw a more wholesome picture of what it was like in Granada and the other cities. <br />I don't think I shall forget this novel for a very long time.</span>
  <a data-text-id="16842570316068711043" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


